    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Egg white protein used in the food industry and in photographic emulsions, particularly those dating to the 19th century. For the more general meaning of the naturally occurring, water-soluble protein found in egg white, milk, and blood, use "albumin (general protein)."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
